sif3.infra.common.env
Class ProviderEnvironmentStoreOperations

java.lang.Object
  sif3.infra.common.env.BaseEnvironmentStoreOperations
      sif3.infra.common.env.ProviderEnvironmentStoreOperations

public class ProviderEnvironmentStoreOperations
extends BaseEnvironmentStoreOperations

Utility class to specifically deal with operations on provider environments and its store. All of the functions are used on the lower levels of this framework and are not expected to be exposed to higher levels where a developer will operate on.

Author:
Joerg Huber

loadEnvironmentForConsumer

public sif3.infra.common.model.EnvironmentType loadEnvironmentForConsumer(java.lang.String envName,
                                                                          java.lang.String consumerID)
This method loads the environment for a given consumer. Before it is loaded it checks if it does already exist. If it doesn't then null is returned, otherwise the environment is returned. Note if it doesn't exist it WON'T create it. To create the environment from a temaplate then the 'createAndStoreEnvForConsumer(...)' method in this class must be called.

Parameters:
envName - The name of the environment to load.
consumerID - The ID of the consumer for which the environment shall be loaded.
Returns:
See desc.

createAndStoreEnvForConsumer

public sif3.infra.common.model.EnvironmentType createAndStoreEnvForConsumer(sif3.infra.common.model.EnvironmentType inputEnv)
This method takes the inputEnv and uses its data to create a new full environment. The reminder of the environment data is read from the template directory (environment services and permissions). A SessionToken and Environment ID is also created before the final environment is stored. The final environment data is then returned. If the environment cannot be created in the environment store then the error is logged and null is returned.

NOTE:
If an environment does already exist for the given consumer then that environment is returned and no new one is created.

Parameters:
inputEnv - The environment as provided by a consumer. This is a cut-down version with minimal data as specified in the SIF3 spec.

deleteEnvironmentForConsumer

public boolean deleteEnvironmentForConsumer(java.lang.String envName,
                                            java.lang.String consumerID)
Remove and environment for a consumer. It is checked if the environment exists and only then it is removed (physically deleted from the environment store!).

Parameters:
envName - The name of the environment to remove.
consumerID - The ID of the consumer for which the environment shall be removed.
Returns:
TRUE: It existed and has been removed. FALSE: Didn't exist or could not be removed (see error.log for details).

isEnvironmentSupportedForConsumer

public boolean isEnvironmentSupportedForConsumer(java.lang.String envName,
                                                 java.lang.String consumerID,
                                                 boolean logError)
This method checks if a consumer is allowed to access an environment of a given name.

Parameters:
envName - The name of the environment to check for.
consumerID - The ID of the consumer for which the environment shall be checked.
logError - Indicate if the consumer has no access to an environment if that fact shall be logged.
Returns:
TRUE: Consumer has access to environment. FALSE: Consumer has no access.
